  "text": "Asakura et al. have investigated the way information is exchanged between evacuees in a disaster. They have constructed a map information sharing system [CITATION_1] . In their system, some evacuees record road information while moving to shelters, and then exchange the information they have collected using a MANET. Since the situation can change from time to time in a disaster area, they have proposed an ACO-based extension to allow evacuees to respond to such changes [CITATION_2] .",
